WEBVTT

00:00.930 --> 00:02.659
MAN:
It-it's about the whole cosmos.

00:02.700 --> 00:05.794
It-it's not just in our heads
or what happens to us.

00:05.830 --> 00:08.333
I mean, we want to make it
about-about crime on the streets

00:08.370 --> 00:11.203
and all that, but it's...

00:11.240 --> 00:14.277
it's not about things,
it's about, um... e-everything.

00:14.310 --> 00:16.403
Right? So, what do you
do about that?

00:16.450 --> 00:18.509
What-what do you do
about everything?

00:20.380 --> 00:22.416
Well, you start
with the broken window theory.

00:22.450 --> 00:25.419
Even one broken window

00:25.450 --> 00:27.680
creates the condition
for antisocial behavior.

00:27.720 --> 00:30.621
I remember a time
when Chicago was different.

00:30.660 --> 00:34.152
When people helped each other.
I remember being a little kid

00:34.200 --> 00:37.294
and playing out on the street,
going trick-or-treating.

00:37.330 --> 00:38.763
I don't think anyone would allow
their child to do that...

00:38.800 --> 00:40.165
No, no, cut the last sentence.

00:40.200 --> 00:41.690
Go back to the other thing
she said.

00:41.740 --> 00:43.833
I remember growing up as
a blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

00:43.870 --> 00:45.428
What, with a jump cut?

00:45.470 --> 00:48.507
No, the "morning
in America" stuff.

00:50.280 --> 00:51.474
What are you doing? Cows?

00:51.510 --> 00:52.738
When were there ever
cows In Chicago?

00:52.780 --> 00:54.316
You said "morning
in America"...

00:54.350 --> 00:55.840
Yeah... kids
playing ball,

00:55.880 --> 00:57.108
water hoses,

00:57.150 --> 00:59.482
Uncle Sam, blah-blah stuff.

01:01.560 --> 01:04.427
And keep
Alicia's voice running.

01:04.460 --> 01:05.779
ALICIA:
I mean, remember being a kid

01:05.830 --> 01:07.627
and playing on the street,

01:07.660 --> 01:09.423
going trick-or-treating...
Then go to the hug.

01:09.470 --> 01:11.358
Yeah, sure.

01:11.400 --> 01:13.539
Let's try it with,
uh, the guitar under it.

01:13.570 --> 01:15.458
EDITOR: Okay...
(guitar playing gentle tune)

01:15.500 --> 01:17.536
ALICIA:
I remember being a kid
and playing on the street,

01:17.570 --> 01:19.060
going trick-or-treating.

01:20.810 --> 01:23.506
Ah! Everybody
likes Alicia, see?

01:23.550 --> 01:26.178
Uh, have the cosmos idiot nod
his head. There was something

01:26.220 --> 01:28.370
where he was nodding his head.
He has a nervous tic.
He's always nodding his head.

01:28.420 --> 01:29.717
What do I care?
What are you, his physician?

01:33.160 --> 01:36.152
ALICIA:
I remember being a kid
and playing on the street,

01:36.190 --> 01:38.488
going trick-or-treating.

01:38.530 --> 01:40.828
Yeah.._. even the cosmos
Idiot agrees.

01:40.860 --> 01:42.828
Uh, then cut to Peter,

01:42.870 --> 01:45.566
and, uh, keep
the guitar going.

01:45.600 --> 01:48.433
...playing on the street,
going trick-or-treating.

01:48.470 --> 01:49.562
PETER:
The key is caring

01:49.610 --> 01:52.579
and Alicia cares.

01:52.610 --> 01:56.398
I think the job of a state's
attorney is so overwhelming,

01:56.450 --> 01:59.647
that it needs a person whose
heart is in the right place.

01:59.680 --> 02:01.819
And do you have a take on
Frank Prady, Mr. Governor?

02:01.850 --> 02:03.738
Uh, just tell me what you
want me to say and then

02:03.790 --> 02:05.917
I'll just say it.
Uh, Alicia as an
experienced candidate.

02:05.950 --> 02:07.611
Peter, uh, don't go
too hard on Prady.

02:07.660 --> 02:08.809
There_are_
legal ramifications.

02:08.860 --> 02:09.884
Whenever you're ready,
Mr. Governor.

02:09.930 --> 02:11.522
I like Frank Prady,

02:11.560 --> 02:12.754
but if there was ever a time

02:12.800 --> 02:14.529
for a state's attorney who has

02:14.560 --> 02:16.528
experience and compassion...

02:16.570 --> 02:18.299
it's now.
Good. Use that as a transition

02:18.330 --> 02:19.797
to the shooting;
the news footage.

02:19.840 --> 02:22.161
Mm-hmm, make it black
and white, grainy.

02:24.210 --> 02:26.303
Go music.
Go to the Irish music.

02:26.340 --> 02:28.638
(upbeat Irish music playing)

02:28.680 --> 02:30.545
Great, yeah, that's it, a-a
festive courthouse shooting!

02:30.580 --> 02:31.899
What are you-- an idiot?

02:31.950 --> 02:35.317
The Irish wake music,
the keening music.

02:37.350 --> 02:40.808
(somber Irish music playing)

02:40.860 --> 02:42.555
Good. Now, go
to the Finn interview.

02:42.590 --> 02:45.423
I don't really
like going into it.

02:45.460 --> 02:49.294
JOHNNY:
This is for Alicia,
so anything you can tell us.

02:49.330 --> 02:52.197
I was in court
across from WIll...

02:52.240 --> 02:53.662
Could you use
his full name?

02:53.700 --> 02:55.668
Yeah.

02:55.700 --> 02:58.601
I was in _court
across from WIll Gardner.

02:58.640 --> 03:00.870
We were at sidebar
with the judge

03:00.910 --> 03:01.934
when there was a gunshot.

03:01.980 --> 03:04.869
Will was dying.

03:04.910 --> 03:06.571
And that's where you go,
and you say

03:06.620 --> 03:07.917
sadness blah, blah,
blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

03:07.950 --> 03:08.974
And then we cut back

03:09.020 --> 03:10.419
to the diner op.

03:10.450 --> 03:12.486
ALICIA: The murder rates
are just Insane.

03:12.520 --> 03:14.215
I tried to stop the bleeding,
but I couldn't.

03:14.260 --> 03:15.955
So I just sat there with him,

03:15.990 --> 03:17.753
waiting for the paramedics
to arrive.

03:17.790 --> 03:18.757
I watched the life

03:18.790 --> 03:19.757
of this man, this good man,

03:19.800 --> 03:21.449
fade away because he was

03:21.500 --> 03:23.365
trying to help someone.

03:23.400 --> 03:24.662
Are you really thinking
of using this?

03:24.700 --> 03:25.792
We're not just
thinking of using it.

03:25.830 --> 03:26.899
We're using it.

03:26.940 --> 03:28.430
(groans)
It's so crass. It's awful.

03:28.470 --> 03:30.506
I'm sorry, who are you
again? Who is she?

03:30.540 --> 03:32.770
I'm the body woman.
Then what are you doing talking?

03:32.810 --> 03:34.437
Alicia, this video is meant
to introduce you; the public

03:34.480 --> 03:36.471
doesn't know you. We need
to tell them your story.

03:36.510 --> 03:38.239
The shooting is a
part of your story.

03:38.280 --> 03:41.249
Yeah, but it's so corny
with the boo-hoo-hoo music.

03:41.280 --> 03:42.918
(laughs) I'm sorry, how many
campaigns have you run?

03:42.950 --> 03:44.611
No, seriously.

03:44.650 --> 03:47.312
How many?
Okay, okay.
Tell the scandal stuff.

03:47.360 --> 03:49.009
Tell them
how I raised my kids...
No, this says

03:49.060 --> 03:51.551
why you're running now. You were
personally touched by murder.

03:51.590 --> 03:53.251
Do you think Prady's
gonna have

03:53.300 --> 03:54.722
any trouble talking
about the death of his dad?

03:54.760 --> 03:56.660
With the photos of the car
accident and him crying?

03:56.700 --> 03:58.691
He's up by three points,
we have no media budget...

03:58.730 --> 03:59.958
How about the music
from Titanic?

04:00.000 --> 04:01.831
You could even cut
to shots from Titanic.

04:01.870 --> 04:03.030
Johnny, I'm losing it.
I'm losing it here!

04:03.070 --> 04:05.038
Alicia, we want this
to go viral online.

04:05.070 --> 04:06.628
So, that can't happen
unless it's dramatic.

04:06.680 --> 04:07.829
Okay, so...

04:07.880 --> 04:09.575
use the the comparative ad.

04:09.610 --> 04:10.645
Where's the comparative ad?
We're still waiting

04:10.680 --> 04:12.443
on the full oppo
research on Prady.

04:12.480 --> 04:14.744
And... I need you to call Peter.

04:14.780 --> 04:16.645
To set up a joint interview
for the two of you for tomorrow.

04:16.690 --> 04:19.011
We need a joint interview?
If you want people

04:19.050 --> 04:20.984
to stop asking questions
about your marriage, yeah.
(cell phone ringing)

04:21.020 --> 04:24.057
Yeah, Diane.

04:24.090 --> 04:26.320
Sorry, I can't make it.

04:26.360 --> 04:28.499
She can't make it.
Why not?

04:28.530 --> 04:29.519
Alicia, I'll have to call
you back. He's here.

04:29.570 --> 04:30.923
Good morning.

04:30.970 --> 04:33.393
My name is Stu Harper.
I am the Special Agent

04:33.440 --> 04:36.034
in charge of the Chicago
FBI field office.

04:36.070 --> 04:37.537
I was hoping we could

04:37.570 --> 04:38.867
just have a moment to talk

04:38.910 --> 04:40.070
before anyone shouts

04:40.110 --> 04:41.634
"attorney/client privilege"

04:41.680 --> 04:43.944
or "grand jury subpoena"
at each other.

04:43.980 --> 04:45.402
Well, that's good news,
Agent Harper,

04:45.450 --> 04:46.747
because I don't shout.

04:46.780 --> 04:48.475
Good-- we're making
progress already.

04:48.520 --> 04:51.080
We need your help, Cary.

04:51.120 --> 04:53.680
We are investigating
Lemond Bishop

04:53.720 --> 04:55.608
and his drug empire,
and we need your help

04:55.660 --> 04:57.480
building a case.
Unfortunately,

04:57.530 --> 04:59.828
Mr. Agos was one
of Mr. Bishop's attorneys,

04:59.860 --> 05:01.691
so he can't...
I understand.

05:01.730 --> 05:03.425
And I know you're being
prosecuted by

05:03.470 --> 05:04.425
the State's Attorney's office,
Cary.

05:04.470 --> 05:05.869
We sympathize.

05:05.900 --> 05:07.561
I want you to know
that our investigation

05:07.600 --> 05:08.760
has nothing to do with theirs.

05:08.800 --> 05:09.960
Oh, great.
In fact,

05:10.010 --> 05:11.102
we want to help you.

05:11.140 --> 05:12.971
Agent Delaney.

05:13.010 --> 05:15.979
Please meet Cary Agos
and Diane Lockhart.

05:16.010 --> 05:18.046
LANA: Yes, we've had
dealings before.

05:19.620 --> 05:20.848
Nice to see you again.

05:20.880 --> 05:22.484
HARPER:
I think you'll agree these are

05:22.520 --> 05:23.839
highly unusual circumstances--

05:23.890 --> 05:25.983
an FBI agent playing you

05:26.020 --> 05:27.658
one of our wiretaps.

05:27.690 --> 05:29.988
But we have a good reason.

05:30.030 --> 05:31.383
Lana?

05:31.430 --> 05:32.590
BISHOP (staticky):
I can't move.

05:32.630 --> 05:33.790
I can't do business.

05:33.830 --> 05:34.990
They're crawling up my ass.

05:35.030 --> 05:36.361
MAN:
It's not a dead end.

05:36.400 --> 05:37.992
BISHOP:
Then why am I drowning here?

05:38.030 --> 05:40.760
MAN: You know why-- the lawyer.
Cary Agos.

05:40.800 --> 05:42.358
Look, we're not saying
he flipped, Lemond.

05:42.410 --> 05:43.468
But the cops smell blood here.

05:43.510 --> 05:45.000
MAN 2:
We're seen as weak.

05:45.040 --> 05:46.871
BISHOP: Then what do we do?
He's a white lawyer.

05:46.910 --> 05:49.549
People take notice.
He can't just disappear.

05:49.580 --> 05:52.469
(static crackling)

05:52.520 --> 05:54.476
MAN:
One to the back of the head.

05:54.520 --> 05:56.784
(static crackling)

05:57.990 --> 05:59.912
BISHOP:
Okay. I want it done.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.518
Next week.

06:01.560 --> 06:03.448
Make this end.
MAN: You're sure?

06:03.490 --> 06:06.084
BISHOP: Phone me when you got a
plan, where and how because I...

06:06.130 --> 06:08.724
(static crackling)

06:08.760 --> 06:11.627
That's it.
That's an official FBI wiretap

06:11.670 --> 06:14.093
of Lemond Bishop discussing
how to murder you, Cary.

06:14.140 --> 06:15.835
DIANE: When was
it recorded?

06:15.870 --> 06:17.167
_ LANA:
Five days ago.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.838
Thursday the 13th
at Bishop's house.

06:19.880 --> 06:22.769
The time frame they're
discussing for your murder

06:22.810 --> 06:24.448
is this week.

06:24.480 --> 06:26.038
Uh, we'd like
a copy of the tape.

06:26.080 --> 06:27.445
HARPER: N0.

06:27.480 --> 06:28.742
It's in both our interests

06:28.780 --> 06:30.543
to put Mr. Bishop away.

06:30.590 --> 06:32.080
So, help us prosecute him.

06:32.120 --> 06:34.156
Go arrest him.

06:34.190 --> 06:36.181
If Mr. Bishop is threatening me,

06:36.220 --> 06:38.723
go arrest him.

06:38.760 --> 06:40.455
Why do you need me?

06:40.500 --> 06:42.559
Uh, Mr. Bishop and
his lieutenants were

06:42.600 --> 06:44.568
very careful in
what they said.

06:44.600 --> 06:45.828
It's not enough
for an arrest.

06:45.870 --> 06:47.599
But it is enough for you

06:47.640 --> 06:48.629
to be very,
very worried.

06:48.670 --> 06:51.537
Okay. Thank you.

06:51.570 --> 06:53.128
Uh, Cary,

06:53.180 --> 06:55.978
he's talking about
murdering you this week.

06:56.010 --> 06:58.046
A little hint
for next time you do this:

06:58.080 --> 07:00.219
Don't have the woman who's
sleeping with my girlfriend

07:00.250 --> 07:02.115
break it to me.
HARPER:
You're... I'm sorry, what?

07:02.150 --> 07:04.448
Next time you try to get me
to flip, don't use her.

07:08.520 --> 07:10.522
(elevator bell dings)

07:10.560 --> 07:12.448
It's a fake.

07:12.500 --> 07:14.923
Bishop was out of town
in Florida on the 13th.

07:14.960 --> 07:16.769
Even if you're right, you need
to act like you're wrong.

07:16.800 --> 07:18.461
Bishop could threaten
something like that.

07:18.500 --> 07:20.730
No, you're right.
What do we do?

07:20.770 --> 07:22.806
_ DIANE: _
Kalinda, hand your ongomg cases

07:22.840 --> 07:24.808
to Robyn.

07:24.840 --> 07:26.876
The FBI played us
a tape this morning

07:26.910 --> 07:28.207
of Bishop threatening Cary.

07:28.240 --> 07:30.208
Threatening him with what?

07:30.250 --> 07:31.877
Assassination.

07:31.910 --> 07:33.639
He's worried Cary
will turn on him.

07:33.680 --> 07:36.649
Cary thinks that
the tape was fake,

07:36.690 --> 07:39.045
cobbled together from
other wiretaps, but

07:39.090 --> 07:41.957
I need to be sure.
What do you think?

07:41.990 --> 07:44.049
Bishop may want him dead.

07:44.090 --> 07:45.489
I would agree.

07:45.530 --> 07:46.792
Cary says that Bishop was

07:46.830 --> 07:48.525
out of town on November 13

07:48.560 --> 07:50.061
when the tape was
recorded at his house.

07:50.100 --> 07:51.499
Could you check that out?
Yeah.

07:51.530 --> 07:52.667
Uh...

07:52.700 --> 07:54.793
we need to hire Cary
a bodyguard.

07:54.840 --> 07:56.193
Can you do that?
Sure.

07:56.240 --> 07:58.834
Court says I can't be
within 30 feet of him,

07:58.870 --> 07:59.939
so I'll need your help.

07:59.980 --> 08:01.732
Whatever you need.

08:01.780 --> 08:03.771
Alicia!

08:07.220 --> 08:08.869
Mr. Prady.

08:08.920 --> 08:10.740
Frank. Hello.

08:10.790 --> 08:11.939
I didn't think we had...

08:11.990 --> 08:12.979
Uh, an appointment, no.

08:13.020 --> 08:14.055
I didn't want to get

08:14.090 --> 08:15.250
into all the mess of that.

08:15.290 --> 08:16.279
Uh, do you have a minute?

08:16.320 --> 08:17.787
I do.

08:17.830 --> 08:19.855
But I'm not sure
this is such a good idea.

08:19.900 --> 08:21.925
I know. My campaign manager
would kill me if he knew.

08:21.960 --> 08:25.521
But, uh, let's
live dangerously.

08:25.570 --> 08:28.596
Before James Castro left
the race, he gave me this.

08:28.640 --> 08:29.868
What is it?
It's dirt.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.559
On you, your husband,

08:31.610 --> 08:33.168
your children,
your family.

08:33.210 --> 08:34.632
I haven't opened it.

08:34.680 --> 08:35.829
He wanted me to
use it against you.

08:35.880 --> 08:37.108
But I won't.

08:39.210 --> 08:41.314
I want to do this differently.

08:41.350 --> 08:43.545
I want to not pound
you into submission.

08:43.590 --> 08:44.989
And I don't want
you to pound me.

08:45.020 --> 08:46.908
I've heard politicians
in the past agree

08:46.960 --> 08:48.655
they won't go negative,
and they always

08:48.690 --> 08:50.123
go negative, and
I think I know why.

08:50.160 --> 08:51.252
Because it works?

08:51.290 --> 08:53.554
No, because it's a posture.

08:53.600 --> 08:54.953
They don't mean it
when they say it.

08:55.000 --> 08:57.628
Otherwise they'd go to
the other candidate,

08:57.670 --> 08:59.262
not the press.
That's why I'm here.

08:59.300 --> 09:00.961
I'm not going to the press.

09:01.000 --> 09:05.004
I'm coming to you to say
I will not go negative.

09:05.040 --> 09:07.076
And I'm asking you
to do the same.

09:07.110 --> 09:09.943
Now, my campaign manager,

09:09.980 --> 09:12.073
if he were here, Frank,

09:12.110 --> 09:15.011
would say you're up
three points in the polls.

09:15.050 --> 09:17.939
Of course you want to suspend
negative campaigning.

09:17.990 --> 09:19.287
Yeah, but...

09:19.320 --> 09:21.208
you must have the
same projections I do.

09:21.260 --> 09:22.682
The race will tighten.

09:22.730 --> 09:24.027
You have women voters,

09:24.060 --> 09:25.618
I have African-Americans.

09:25.660 --> 09:28.220
You have Catholics,
I have limousine liberals.

09:28.260 --> 09:30.091
That's a flipped-coin of a race.

09:30.130 --> 09:32.166
I like betting.
I wouldn't bet on it.

09:32.200 --> 09:34.691
Wouldn't you rather win
without bloodying

09:34.740 --> 09:35.764
each other in the process?

09:35.800 --> 09:36.960
I don't have
an opinion on that.

09:37.010 --> 09:38.238
I doubt that.

09:38.270 --> 09:40.329
That's your right.

09:41.810 --> 09:43.641
This is my number.

09:43.680 --> 09:45.102
My private cell number.

09:45.150 --> 09:47.141
My campaign manager
doesn't even have it.

09:47.180 --> 09:49.171
Whenever you want
to talk, call me.

09:49.220 --> 09:50.312
You shouldn't give me that.

09:50.350 --> 09:51.749
I know.

09:51.790 --> 09:52.950
But there it is.

10:04.970 --> 10:06.164
You're not my enemy, Alicia.

10:06.200 --> 10:07.667
I know.

10:07.700 --> 10:09.702
I'm your opponent.

10:10.910 --> 10:12.901
Call me.

10:12.940 --> 10:14.009
No handlers involved.

10:14.040 --> 10:15.632
No political ops.

10:15.680 --> 10:17.773
Just us.

10:17.810 --> 10:20.074
(door opens)

10:20.120 --> 10:22.076
(door closes)

10:22.120 --> 10:24.384
(elevator whirrs quietly)

10:29.220 --> 10:31.120
(door clacks, rattles)

10:46.710 --> 10:49.235
(rock music playing, muffled,
in a distant apartment)

11:11.170 --> 11:13.195
(phone rings,
Cary sighs)

11:13.240 --> 11:14.867
Yeah?

11:14.900 --> 11:16.162
KALIN DA:
Cary, it's me.

11:16.200 --> 11:17.861
I'm in your apartment.

11:17.910 --> 11:19.400
Okay, he's in.
Come on up.

11:19.440 --> 11:22.000
Kalinda.
You're not supposed to be here.

11:22.040 --> 11:23.200
Look, just
five minutes.

11:23.250 --> 11:24.740
I've hired you

11:24.780 --> 11:26.304
a bodyguard.
I'm fine.

11:26.350 --> 11:28.215
This FBI tap is fake.
Bishop couldn't have

11:28.250 --> 11:29.808
been home when the FBI
said they taped it.

11:29.850 --> 11:31.408
November 13, Cary,
he wa home.

11:31.450 --> 11:32.781
He came back a day
early from Florida.

11:32.820 --> 11:34.219
I have the flight
confirmation.

11:34.260 --> 11:35.784
(knocking at door)

11:35.820 --> 11:37.458
Who is that?
It's your
bodyguard.

11:41.830 --> 11:43.366
KALINDA:
Hey, Carter, how
are you doing?

11:43.400 --> 11:45.163
CARTER:
Good. You want me in?
KALINDA: Yeah.

11:45.200 --> 11:47.088
Cary, this is Carter Grayson.

11:47.140 --> 11:48.437
He's, uh...
Yeah, I know.

