it's real or faked,

29:30.560 --> 29:32.892
but there are no edits.

29:32.930 --> 29:34.534
Is it Bishop's voice?

29:34.570 --> 29:36.037
Get me a tape on him,
I'll tell you positively.

29:36.070 --> 29:37.139
When do you need it?

29:37.170 --> 29:38.307
Now.

29:38.340 --> 29:39.898
Kalinda...
I love you.

29:39.940 --> 29:41.305
I would anything for you,

29:41.340 --> 29:42.898
but I can't bend space and time.

29:42.940 --> 29:44.544
Try.

29:47.180 --> 29:48.511
That was interesting,
last night.

29:48.550 --> 29:49.869
I know.

29:49.920 --> 29:51.547
I'm sorry, I was...
in a weird mood.

29:51.590 --> 29:53.410
And the mood is gone?

29:53.450 --> 29:55.111
The mood is... worrisome.

29:55.160 --> 29:56.286
And why is that?

29:56.320 --> 29:58.857
Because I'm...

29:58.890 --> 30:00.027
I don't know.

30:00.060 --> 30:01.254
I wish things were simpler.

30:01.300 --> 30:03.188
Things can be simpler.

30:03.230 --> 30:05.425
You just need to...
want them to be.

30:05.470 --> 30:06.994
I don't think that's true.

30:07.030 --> 30:08.338
People have expectations.

30:08.370 --> 30:10.190
Which people?

30:13.210 --> 30:16.805
I always hated that
these offices were glass.

30:17.950 --> 30:19.941
Okay, I'm gonna go now.

30:21.950 --> 30:23.440
(phone rings)

30:23.480 --> 30:26.040
This is Alicia.
Hi. We have a problem.

30:26.090 --> 30:28.183
I would expect nothing less.

30:28.220 --> 30:30.927
Prady put out
his ten-minute video.

30:30.960 --> 30:34.327
(someber
My dad...

30:34.360 --> 30:37.056
he was everything to me.

30:37.100 --> 30:38.965
A musician.

30:39.000 --> 30:41.161
Genius. He, uh...
(clears throat)

30:41.200 --> 30:42.929
*

30:42.970 --> 30:45.302
And then on my 16th birthday...

30:45.340 --> 30:48.104
(indistinct radio chatter)

30:48.140 --> 30:51.109
Nice work, not too sappy,
good photos--

30:51.150 --> 30:52.469
someone knows what
they're domg over there.

30:52.510 --> 30:54.068
And here she
is again.

30:54.120 --> 30:56.111
I don't get it--
why are you guys worried?

30:56.150 --> 30:57.617
It's coming up.
Eat some potato chips.

30:57.650 --> 30:59.618
No, I'm fine.
Eat them.
They're good.

30:59.650 --> 31:02.380
PRADY:
I went from my birthday party
right to the hospital.

31:02.420 --> 31:04.251
Uh, I saw him.

31:04.290 --> 31:08.124
I held his hand...
when he was rolled in.

31:08.160 --> 31:10.128
I know it was hard on Frank,

31:10.160 --> 31:12.264
seeing someone die
in front of him.

31:12.300 --> 31:13.528
Uh-oh.

31:13.570 --> 31:15.162
That's my dress.

31:15.200 --> 31:17.168
JOSH: _
Yep. You are wearing
the exact same dress

31:17.200 --> 31:18.303
as Prady's mom.
MARISSA:
Uh-oh.

31:18.340 --> 31:19.409
Maybe nobody'll notice.

31:19.440 --> 31:20.532
What, are you, eight?

31:20.570 --> 31:22.674
Everyone
will notice!

31:22.710 --> 31:25.270
Josh, we have to redo the
