They sent it
out to press.

35:05.930 --> 35:07.761
It will get some play.

35:07.800 --> 35:10.234
It's crude,
but effective.

35:10.270 --> 35:12.158
Their tag-line is intended
to be repeated.

35:14.380 --> 35:15.472
That's awful.

35:15.510 --> 35:17.330
This is his campaign
or his PAC?

35:17.380 --> 35:18.677
His PAC, but you know
they're coordinating.

35:18.710 --> 35:19.779
We're not with our PAC.

35:19.810 --> 35:20.845
We could.
But we're not.

35:20.880 --> 35:23.474
JOHNNY: We want to use
the closeted dinosaur ad.

35:23.520 --> 35:24.919
They went negative first.

35:24.950 --> 35:26.918
I'd do it,
he deserves it.
No.

35:26.950 --> 35:29.282
His PAC went negative
first, he didn't.

35:29.320 --> 35:32.926
Alicia, I'm starting to like
you, but you're new to this.

35:32.960 --> 35:34.928
You think you're bringing
something new to campaigning,

35:34.960 --> 35:36.757
but there is nothing
new under the sun.

35:36.800 --> 35:38.927
Let us help
you win this.

35:38.970 --> 35:41.234
Even the nutty lady thinks
you should hit back.

35:41.270 --> 35:43.238
Thank you for the "nutty lady,"
but he's right.

35:43.270 --> 35:45.261
How's my introductory
ad coming?

35:46.840 --> 35:48.808
And Will was dying.

35:48.840 --> 35:51.274
ALICIA:
I got a call about Will dying.

35:51.310 --> 35:52.800
It was awful.

35:52.850 --> 35:54.408
Just awful.
Ouch.

35:54.450 --> 35:55.519
Yeah, it's not good.

35:55.550 --> 35:56.448
We need to use the dinosaur ad,

35:56.480 --> 35:57.447
or we're gonna lose this.

35:59.350 --> 36:01.318
(door closes)

36:01.360 --> 36:03.351
You know, at some point,

36:03.390 --> 36:06.325
the candidate is the candidate,
the manager is the manager.

36:06.360 --> 36:08.225
Are we at that point?

36:08.260 --> 36:09.488
ALICIA:
Where are we?

36:09.530 --> 36:11.259
What's going on?

36:11.300 --> 36:12.597
It's not me, it's my PAC.

36:12.630 --> 36:13.699
At a certain point,
that doesn't matter.

36:13.730 --> 36:14.697
I've been hit.

36:14.740 --> 36:15.695
I know.

36:15.740 --> 36:16.798
Let me see what I can do.

36:18.440 --> 36:19.464
Do it.

36:19.510 --> 36:20.465
Give me a day.

36:20.510 --> 36:22.569
A day is a year in politics.

36:22.610 --> 36:24.601
JOHNNY:
Yeah, we saw the ad.

36:24.650 --> 36:25.901
It's outrageous.

36:25.950 --> 36:27.303
Alicia no longer
represents Lemond Bishop.

36:27.350 --> 36:28.578
And her firm only represents

36:28.620 --> 36:29.848
Colin Sweeney's
business interests.

36:29.880 --> 36:31.745
MAN: Is that a quote?
It is a quote.

36:31.790 --> 36:33.439
How are you planning
to hit back?

36:33.490 --> 36:35.879
Well, we had a plan, but
Mrs. Florrick intends to rise

36:35.920 --> 36:37.581
above the negativity.
MAN: What do you mean?

36:37.620 --> 36:39.485
I mean I had a devastating ad
on Frank Prady

36:39.530 --> 36:41.521
designed by Josh Mariner.
MAN: The king of slice and dice?

