it was too hot to handle.

36:46.270 --> 36:47.567
MAN: Slip it to me, John.
Can't do it.

36:47.600 --> 36:49.363
Come on, I won't say
where it comes from.

36:49.400 --> 36:51.459
And I'll give you prominent
placement for your next release.

36:51.510 --> 36:53.501
No, this one can never get out.

36:56.810 --> 36:57.879
Okay, sit down.

36:57.910 --> 36:59.468
Can you just give it
to me, please?

36:59.510 --> 37:01.444
Kalinda, sit down there,
or you don't get anything.

37:01.480 --> 37:02.947
Okay, you asked
me to look...

37:02.980 --> 37:05.540
Howell, I know what I asked you,
can you just tell me?

37:05.590 --> 37:07.581
Do you want me to start again?

37:07.620 --> 37:09.019
No, God, please, no.

37:09.060 --> 37:10.755
You gave me the other
wiretaps of Lemond Bishop,

37:10.790 --> 37:12.883
so I compared the
vocal characteristics.

37:12.930 --> 37:14.557
Good,
is the wiretap fake?

37:14.600 --> 37:16.420
I compared both
the timbre...
Howell.

37:16.460 --> 37:17.427
Just tell me.

37:17.460 --> 37:19.428
The wiretap is authentic.

37:19.470 --> 37:21.290
The FBI isn't faking anything.

37:21.340 --> 37:22.398
Bishop wants your lawyer killed.

37:23.800 --> 37:25.358
Don't you want
a rundown...?

37:26.640 --> 37:27.607
Cary?

37:27.640 --> 37:28.607
Where are you?

37:28.640 --> 37:31.905
I'm at Bishop's.

37:31.950 --> 37:33.906
Well, what are you doing there?

37:33.950 --> 37:35.474
Get out.

37:35.520 --> 37:36.771
The tape is real.

37:36.820 --> 37:38.811
Bishop wants you dead.

37:44.890 --> 37:47.552
Cary? Where are you?
CARY: I'm at Bishop's.

37:47.590 --> 37:48.955
Get out.
The tape is real.

37:52.000 --> 37:53.820
Bishop wants you dead.

37:55.600 --> 37:58.728
Where's Carter?

37:58.770 --> 38:00.306
Not here.

38:00.340 --> 38:01.568
He's in the car.

38:01.610 --> 38:02.838
I had him wait there.

38:02.880 --> 38:04.472
DYLAN:
Do you know Rat-a-Tat-Cat?

38:06.910 --> 38:08.047
I will call you back, Kalinda.

38:08.080 --> 38:09.342
Get out of there, Cary.

38:09.380 --> 38:11.348
You get four
cards each.

38:11.390 --> 38:12.379
It's really good,
it's about memory

38:15.020 --> 38:16.510
Cary?

38:18.530 --> 38:20.725
No. No, that's okay.

38:20.760 --> 38:22.523
Good.

38:22.560 --> 38:24.926
You take two cards and you
look at them and you remember.

38:24.970 --> 38:26.028
Actually, Dylan, that was work.

38:26.070 --> 38:27.321
I need to go.

38:27.370 --> 38:29.895
You don't
want to play?

38:29.940 --> 38:31.635
BISHOP: Okay,
that was pointless.

38:31.670 --> 38:33.331
DYLAN: Dad! You
want to play, too?

38:33.370 --> 38:34.530
More than two
people can play.

38:34.580 --> 38:37.378
No, uh, maybe later.

38:37.410 --> 38:38.604
Cary and I
have to talk.

38:38.650 --> 38:39.742
No, we can do it later.

38:39.780 --> 38:41.338
That's okay.

38:41.380 --> 38:43.416
Dad, I just
dealt his cards.

38:43.450 --> 38:45.486
I know,
and Cary wants to play.

38:45.520 --> 38:46.817
But maybe later.

38:46.850 --> 38:48.613
Mr. Bishop,
I just got a call from work.

38:48.660 --> 38:50.651
Cary, I need a minute.

38:50.690 --> 38:51.827
And I wish I had time.

38:53.860 --> 38:55.748
Dylan,

38:55.800 --> 38:58.496
Cary can play
Rat-a-Tat-Cat afterwards.

38:59.630 --> 39:01.598
All right.

39:01.640 --> 39:02.834
Bye, Cary.

39:02.870 --> 39:04.064
Bye, Dylan.

39:07.810 --> 39:09.778
Why do you have
a bodyguard, Cary?

39:09.810 --> 39:12.472
Oh, the firm gave me one.

39:12.510 --> 39:15.343
Why did they give you one?

39:23.590 --> 39:27.082
